Anne Phelan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anne_Phelan 0 Anne Mary Phelan (born 2 August 1948), is an Australian actress, who has appeared in many Australian theatre and television productions, as well as radio and voice-over. She is known for her TV soap opera roles as Myra Desmond in Prisoner (1980–1985) and Monica Taylor in Something in the Air (2000–2002), for which she won the 2000 AFI (AACTA) Award for Best Actress in a Television Drama, having previously won the 1988 AFI Award for Best Actress in a Miniseries for Poor Man's Orange. She received the 2016 Equity Lifetime Achievement Award.
